Mexico didn't have any pumping equipment of its own; it had to import it all and the bulk of it came from the United States. As you can see here, the revolution was bad for business; it interrupted the rail lines and generally made it difficult to gain access to the petroleum fields. But with the revolutionary situation resolved, US investment resumed (note, it's not the Great War that's interrupting investment; it shoots up even during the war).
